  {
    "type": "Question",
    "name": "Question 30 @ 2023/2024",
    "Question": {
      "content": "The plates of a 4.0 F capacitor are separated by a 2.5mm air gap. Calculate the area of the plates (ε₀ = 8.85×10⁻¹² Fm⁻¹)",
      "type": "subJective",
      "options": []
    },
    "Answer": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "2.81 × 10⁶ m²"
    },
    "Explanation": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "<p>The capacitance of a parallel plate capacitor is\\( C =\\frac{\\epsilon_0 A}{d}\\), where\\( C = 4.0\\,\\text{F}\\),\\(\\epsilon_0 = 8.85\\times 10^{-12}\\,\\text{F/m}\\), and\\( d = 2.5\\times 10^{-3}\\,\\text{m}\\). Solving for\\( A\\):\\( A =\\frac{C d}{\\epsilon_0} =\\frac{4.0\\times 2.5\\times 10^{-3}}{8.85\\times 10^{-12}}\\approx 2.81\\times 10^6\\,\\text{m}^2\\).</p>"
    },
    "topic": [
      "Capacitance",
      "Electrostatics",
      "Electric Fields",
      "Dielectric Materials"
    ]
  }
]